(16, 0, '2013-06-19 07:27:04', '', '', 9, '<h6>INTRODUCTION</h6>\r\n\r\n<p>Every year, JAKIN N.G.O organizes an End of the Year Party for Vulnerable children (VC) and other less privileged families. The 2010 inaugural edition, entertained 165 VCs children and 28 caregivers. In 2011, 222 VCs were entertained along with 32 members of Jakin Widows Group (JWG) and 22 members of the Samaritan platform support group (SPSG) while 14 other caregivers also benefitted from the event. \r\nThe organisation scaled up this year as 250 vulnerable children comprising of (126male, 124female), 57 care givers (1male, 56female) and 10 guests were hosted to the event. \r\n</p>', '1026_1371642282', 17, 'REPORT-OF-JAKIN-CHILDRENS-CLUB-END-OF-THE-YEAR-PARTY-2012', 'REPORT OF JAKIN CHILDREN''S CLUB END OF THE YEAR PARTY 2012', '1'),
(17, 0, '2013-06-19 08:13:19', '', '', 9, '<p>OPENING PRAYER: The party started at exactly 12noon, instead of the scheduled 11: am, due to the delay caused by rain. The opening prayer was said by Orogbemi Amos (J.C.C member)<br>\r\n WELCOME ADDRESS: The welcome address was given by Mr. Olumide Akinosho of Jakin N.G.O and in attendance were thirty-four care givers (1 male, 33 female), two hundred (200) children which consist of one hundred and eight (108 female) &nbsp;and ninety-two (92) male.<br>\r\n OPENING REMARK/ INTRODUCTION OF GUEST: The opening remark and introduction of special guests was done by Mrs. Adebiyi Olubukola, President of JAKIN N.G.O. She further introduced the following guests on the high table- Pastor Chibuzor Ayanwun and Sister Deola from The Saints Christian Centre. For lots of fun and excitement the children enjoyed lots of music and Five (5) different games divided into two segments. <br>\r\n FIRST SEGMENT: SETTING AND THROWING OF BALLS: The setting and throwing of balls was done among the children of ages 7-10yrs old. Three persons per four groups were chosen and four children were declared winners. The winners went home with various gifts.</p>', '1027_1371645167', 17, 'Jakins-Childrens-day-report-2012', 'Jakin\\''s Children\\''s day report 2012', '1'),
