(20, 0, '2013-06-26 09:20:57', '', '', 3, '<p>2013 DRESS A CHILD FOR SCHOOL PROJECT IS HERE! 800 partners are urgently needed to help dress 400\r\norphans &amp; vulnerable for school @ N7,500 each to commemorate September 8th\r\nInternational literacy day. Don\\''t let this opportunity to bless a child pass\r\nyou by. Please call Sanya - 08027884221 or pay directly into GTB current\r\naccount of JAKINMINIS N.G.O, 0010499020, Alagomeji branch. Thank you.</p>', '1030_1372254229', 0, 'Dress-a-Child-for-School-Project-2013', 'Dress a Child for School Project 2013', '0'),
(21, 0, '2013-06-27 15:54:26', '', '', 5, '<p>The 2<sup>nd</sup> batch of JAKIN N.G.O\r\nFresh Foundation Project (FFP) scholarship for indigent youths is now in\r\nprogress. The batch commenced lectures on Saturday, 9<sup>th</sup> June, 2013\r\nwith 40 participants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>FFP is an initiative of JAKIN N.G.O\r\ndesigned to empower indigent youths in the lower class of Lagos youths between\r\nages 15 to 35 years with <strong><em>Basic Business Management principles and re\r\n orientation skills</em></strong>. &nbsp;This\r\ngrassroot business school is a highly subsidized 3 months training which holds\r\nonce a week (4hrs) to change their poor perception of life, reform their minds\r\nand empower them with necessary skills to enable them build or contribute positively\r\nto the growth of businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 1<sup>st</sup> batch of the training\r\nwas successfully completed with 84 participants, who graduated on 30<sup>th</sup>\r\nMay, 2013. This new batch is expected to graduate at the end of August.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, forms are still on sale at <strong><s>N</s></strong> 600 to fill the remaining\r\nspaces in this present batch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information, please call the Mr\r\nMayokun on 08099902845</p>', '1031_1372364371', 12, '2ND-BATCH-OF-FRESH-FOUNDATION-PROJECT-3-MONTHS-SCHOLARSHIP-SCHEME-FOR-INDIGENT-YOUTHS-COMMENCES-LECTURES', '2ND BATCH OF FRESH FOUNDATION PROJECT 3 MONTHS SCHOLARSHIP SCHEME FOR INDIGENT YOUTHS COMMENCES LECTURES', '0'),
(22, 0, '2013-06-27 16:09:04', '', '', 5, '<p>Everyone Has Something To Give Initiative\r\n(E2GIVE) of Human Leadership Resources limited represented by Mr Kehinde made a\r\ndonation of 101 cartons of Indomie noodles to Jakin Childrens Club (JCC) for\r\norphans and vulnerable children as nutritional support&nbsp; for the June 2013 edition of their monthly\r\nmeeting. The meeting focusing on Morals  Children and TV was held on 22<sup>nd</sup>\r\nJune 2013 between 11am and 1pm. Over 300 children benefitted from this kind\r\ngesture.</p>', '1031_1372364666', 12, 'E2GIVE-DONATES-101-CARTONS-OF-INDOMIE', 'E2GIVE DONATES 101 CARTONS OF INDOMIE', '0'),
(23, 0, '2013-06-28 07:48:07', '', '', 5, '<p>I was\r\nso thrilled yesterday afternoon, when I met Jakin beneficiary - Mrs Sade selling\r\nliquid soap she made after the soap making empowerment training conducted by\r\nJakin. <br><br>She now sustains her 4 children with d profit made. I pray the lord\r\nempowers JAKIN with grace to do more</p>', '1033_1372421724', 13, 'Mrs-Sade-selling-Luquid-Soap', 'Mrs Sade selling Luquid Soap', '0'),
