(26, 0, '2013-06-28 13:05:29', '', '', 4, ' <p>JAKIN N.G.O is registered as Jakinminis International Company limited by guarantee (RC 629819). It was established on October 12th, 2003 by Mrs Adebiyi Olubukola nee Akinlosotu to solve some of the social issues in our society.<br>\r\n         <strong>Our KEY FOCUS AREAS</strong> are health, education and entrepreneurship, while our <strong>TARGET POPULATION</strong> are vulnerable groups such as Orphans and Vulnerable Children (OVC&rsquo;s), Widows, People Living with HIV/Aids (PLWHA&rsquo;s) and youths.<strong></strong></p>\r\n        <p><strong>OUR VISION </strong>is a global village devoid of poverty and its consequences while our <strong>MISSION </strong>is to work with vulnerable groups in Africa to overcome economic, educational and health hardships.</p>\r\n        <p>Our <strong>GOAL </strong>is that<strong> </strong>vulnerable groups have sufficient empowerment to efficiently and effectively fight poverty and its consequences.</p>\r\n        <p><strong>Our VALUES </strong>are<strong> </strong>transparency,<strong> </strong>integrity<strong>, </strong>humility<strong>, </strong>passion and the fear of God while <strong>our STRATEGIES</strong><strong> </strong>are<strong> </strong>community mobilization<strong>, </strong>resource mobilization<strong>, </strong>networking and<strong> </strong>capacity building.</p>\r\n        <p>Our head quarters consisting of a 6 member board of Directors and a staff strength of 18 is in Lagos State while we have a branch in Zamfara state manned by youth corpers. The HQ has over 300 active volunteers and over 1000 financial and material individual partners.</p>\r\n        <p>Since inception the organisation has enjoyed ample <strong>MEDIA EXPOSURE</strong>. We have featured 16 times in various National dailies, 5 times in magazines, 4 times on radio, 15 times on National television stations, 6 times on International and cable stations excluding repeat broadcasts as at November 2012. They include interviews on Moments with Mo, Today&rsquo;s Woman Magazine, 30mins interview by Journalist from NTA International, 30mins documentary by Journalist from NTA channel 2 aired on NTA Network, 10mins documentary by TV Continental, 30mins interview on Inspiration FM, full page articles in Business day, Guardian among other newspapers and features on Superscreen news.</p>\r\n        <p><strong> </strong><strong> </strong></p>', '1036_1372440917', 14, 'Our-Profile', 'Our Profile', '0'),
(27, 0, '2013-06-28 13:23:08', '', '', 4, ' <p>Our<strong> </strong><strong>LINKAGES/ AFFILIATIONS </strong>i.e agencies collaborated with include<strong> </strong> LSACA (Lagos State Aids Control Agency), LACA (Local Government Aids Control Agency)<strong>, </strong>WAPA ( Ministry of Women Affairs and Poverty Alleviation).<strong> </strong><br>\r\nWe are registered members of the following<strong> National CSO NETWORK COALITIONS</strong>: </p>\r\n        \r\n          <p>AONN (Associations for Orphans and Vulnerable Children N.G.O&rsquo;s in Nigeria)</p>\r\n          <p>CISHAN (Civil Society for HIV and Aids in Nigeria)</p>\r\n          <p>NACCRAN (National Council of Child Rights Advocates of Nigeria) </p>\r\n          <p>ACOMIN (Association for Civil Organization on Malaria, Immunization and Nutrition)</p>\r\n          <p>HURINET (Human Right Information Network)</p>\r\n          <p>TB NETWORK (Tuberculosis Network)</p>\r\n          <p>NYNETHA (Youth Network on HIV/Aids)</p>\r\n          <p>NNGO (Nigerian Network of NGOs)</p>\r\n          <p> CPN (Child Protection Network - UNICEF) </p>', '1037_1372441847', 25, 'Linkages--Affiliations', 'Linkages & Affiliations', '0'),
